    <methods>
      <methodStep>
        <description>          <para>Monthly averages from April 1989 onwards were calculated using the "Daily averaged weather timeseries for Palmer Station" dataset #28, available as knb-lter-pal.28.  A python script (see attached) was used to group and average daily measurements for each month.  The mean and count of measurements is included in this dataset, along with the monthly sum for precipitation.  Dates shown are the start date for each averaging period, i.e. the first of each month.  Historical temperature data (from 1974-1989) was then prepended to the dataset.</para>
          <para></para>
          <para>Before calculating the monthly averages, "Trace" measurements in the precipitation column were converted to zeros, and any gaps in the daily average temperature or pressure columns were filled in with a simple average of the daily high/low measurements, where available.</para>
          <para></para>
          <para>Daily averages have been calculated a variety of ways over the years, including manual readings of high/low measurements in the 80's, to 4x daily measurements in the 90's, and then averages of automatically collected 1-2 minute data after Nov. 2001.  Instrumentation has also changed over that time.  Thus, care must be taken when interpreting monthly averages.  See the AMRC archive for additional information.</para>
</description>
      </methodStep>
    </methods>
